# User Setup and Permissions

### 1- Create a new user
```shell
sudo adduser hamedy
```

### 2- Add the user to the sudo group
```shell
sudo usermod -aG sudo hamedy
```

### 3- Switch to the new user
```shell
su hamedy
```

### 4- Navigate to the user's home directory
```shell
cd /home/hamedy/
```

### 5- Change directory permissions
```shell
sudo chmod -R o+rx /home/hamedy/
```

- Note: Replace `hamedy` with the desired username.